Hundreds of homeless people in Cape Town have been given new homes for the three-week lockdown. Around 230 homeless people have been provided with temporary shelter by the City of Cape Town under a bridge in the city's CBD. The City has provided many of them with tents, mobile toilets and food, as part of efforts to curb the spread of Covid-19. Around 230 homeless people have been provided with temporary shelter by the City of Cape Town under a bridge in the city's CBD.